font.font:
Any information with a
spatial component like a coordinate or a city name can be put on a map and become
geodata. We can do exactly that with GIS!

div.b: Visualisation, Organisation and processing of spatial data:
div.p:
To connect information
to maps is not enough. We need to bring the geodata into a usable structure and in many cases (Organisation), we need to make changes to the data so they can serve our purposes (Processing). Furthermore, it is imperative to visualise the geodata in a way so we can communicate the relevant information (Visualisation).

p.b: Spatial Analyses to reveal connections between spatial data features:

div.p:
Simply visualizing
data falls short of its full potential. We can unlock deeper insights by
applying various analysis techniques to gain a comprehensive understanding of
situations and circumstances.
